HEADWORD: Polypite
<hw>Pol"y*pite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the feeding zooids, or
polyps, of a coral, hydroid, or siphonophore; a hydranth. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Campanularian</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Sometimes, the manubrium of a hydroid medusa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A fossil coral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyplacophora</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
